179
00:07:47.780 --> 00:07:49.060
It was absolutely terrifying.

180
00:07:49.060 --> 00:07:50.540
Thankfully they sat all the kids down

181
00:07:50.540 --> 00:07:51.860
and we weren't kind of wandering around,

182
00:07:51.860 --> 00:07:53.580
you know, knocking into things.

183
00:07:53.580 --> 00:07:56.500
But it was absolutely pitch black

184
00:07:58.100 --> 00:08:00.540
and they turned the lights back on.

185
00:08:00.540 --> 00:08:02.860
But there are lots of cave rescue stories out there

186
00:08:03.060 --> 00:08:05.380
that start with, you know, everything was fine

187
00:08:05.380 --> 00:08:08.020
until the battery went out on the flashlight

188
00:08:08.020 --> 00:08:10.580
and people didn't think to bring a spare set of batteries

189
00:08:10.580 --> 00:08:12.180
or a spare flashlight.

190
00:08:12.180 --> 00:08:13.020
You could read stories.

191
00:08:13.020 --> 00:08:16.060
I read stories from a cave rescuer

192
00:08:16.060 --> 00:08:18.580
who said like in a very short span of time

193
00:08:18.580 --> 00:08:21.740
he rescued two different boys from two different caves

194
00:08:21.740 --> 00:08:25.020
who were within 100 yards of the mouth of the cave

195
00:08:25.020 --> 00:08:27.620
where they'd gone in but their lights had gone out

196
00:08:27.620 --> 00:08:29.620
