Remember the question that said, well, who sinned?

529
00:22:56.680 --> 00:22:58.200
Was it this man or his parents?

530
00:22:58.200 --> 00:23:00.560
Well, was it his sin?

531
00:23:00.560 --> 00:23:02.000
Is that the reason he was born blind?

532
00:23:02.000 --> 00:23:03.160
Or was it his parents sinned

533
00:23:03.160 --> 00:23:05.640
that caused him to be born blind?

534
00:23:05.640 --> 00:23:06.960
The answer was it was neither.

535
00:23:06.960 --> 00:23:10.880
In fact, they were making a kind of categorical error.

536
00:23:10.880 --> 00:23:14.320
And Jesus points this error out to them.

537
00:23:14.320 --> 00:23:16.000
And this is a kind of a side note here,

538
00:23:16.000 --> 00:23:18.240
but just to, it's good for us to get to grips with this.

539
00:23:18.240 --> 00:23:22.040
Their error is assuming that when bad things happen to people,

540
00:23:22.040 --> 00:23:26.800
it must be because of a specific thing that they did wrong.

541
00:23:26.800 --> 00:23:29.400
Right, that there's a kind of one for one there.

542
00:23:29.400 --> 00:23:32.880
So like if this bad thing's happening to you,

543
00:23:32.880 --> 00:23:33.920
you've gotten sick or whatever,

544
00:23:33.920 --> 00:23:37.400
you must have a specific sin that has caused this.

545
00:23:37.400 --> 00:23:39.220
Now it is true in a general sense

546
00:23:39.220 --> 00:23:41.320
that the brokenness that has come into the world

547
00:23:41.320 --> 00:23:43.920
and the hardship, the suffering that we experience

548
00:23:43.920 --> 00:23:46.720
is ultimately because of sin.

549
00:23:46.720 --> 00:23:48.880
God created a perfect world and sin into the world

550
00:23:48.880 --> 00:23:50.880
and that's the way we have the suffering and brokenness

551
00:23:50.880 --> 00:23:52.000
in front of us.

552
00:23:52.880 --> 00:23:55.920
But it is wrong to assume that a specific hardship

553
00:23:55.920 --> 00:23:58.160
is always punishment for a specific sin.

554
00:23:58.160 --> 00:24:00.320
That was the error of Job's friends

555
00:24:00.320 --> 00:24:02.240
if you read the book of Job.

556
00:24:02.240 --> 00:24:04.360
And it is the error of the disciples here

557
00:24:04.360 --> 00:24:05.720
because Jesus makes it clear.

558
00:24:05.720 --> 00:24:08.480
It is not because of any of his specific sins.

559
00:24:10.240 --> 00:24:13.160
So as a side note, don't make the same mistake

560
00:24:13.160 --> 00:24:15.840
either with yourself or maybe with a counsel

561
00:24:15.880 --> 00:24:17.400
you give to others.

562
00:24:17.400 --> 00:24:19.920
Jesus says, no, he is blind actually.

563
00:24:19.920 --> 00:24:22.120
So that, this is verse three,

564
00:24:22.120 --> 00:24:26.040
so that the works of God might be displayed in him.

565
00:24:26.040 --> 00:24:28.960
God has got a unique work that he is going to do

566
00:24:28.960 --> 00:24:30.640
through his life.

567
00:24:30.640 --> 00:24:32.940
He's gonna display his glory.

568
00:24:32.940 --> 00:24:34.920
So how does Jesus do it?

569
00:24:36.920 --> 00:24:38.060
I don't know if anybody saw this coming.

570
00:24:38.060 --> 00:24:40.000
He spat on the ground.

571
00:24:40.000 --> 00:24:42.080
He then went down to the ground.

572
00:24:42.080 --> 00:24:44.440
He started making some mud with the ground

573
00:24:44.440 --> 00:24:47.600
and he takes that mud and he sticks it on the man's eyes

574
00:24:47.600 --> 00:24:49.560
and he calls him to go and wash.

575
00:24:49.560 --> 00:24:52.120
And you read this and you think,

576
00:24:52.120 --> 00:24:54.520
what in the world is he doing?

577
00:24:54.520 --> 00:24:55.960
I know I was reading through this, I was thinking,

578
00:24:55.960 --> 00:24:57.600
I don't know what is going on here?

579
00:24:57.600 --> 00:24:59.080
What, why is he using this mud?

580
00:24:59.080 --> 00:25:00.760
And you kind of read different ideas

581
00:25:00.760 --> 00:25:01.720
people have about it.

582
00:25:01.720 --> 00:25:03.000
And some people say, well,

583
00:25:03.000 --> 00:25:05.040
well it shows us that Jesus uses means.

584
00:25:05.040 --> 00:25:06.960
Like if he uses mud, he can use you

585
00:25:06.960 --> 00:25:08.080
and that kind of thing.

586
00:25:08.080 --> 00:25:09.800
And I don't know, that's true.

587
00:25:10.720 --> 00:25:12.800
Or maybe he was just trying to agitate the Pharisees.

588
00:25:12.800 --> 00:25:14.120
You see that happen a bit later on,

589
00:25:14.120 --> 00:25:16.280
you know, because he's working on the Sabbath day

590
00:25:16.280 --> 00:25:17.920
and that's what makes them mad.

591
00:25:17.920 --> 00:25:19.880
And that could be the case.

592
00:25:21.040 --> 00:25:25.680
But remember, there's something going on here in John.

593
00:25:25.680 --> 00:25:30.280
John is, there's a kind of a creation motif, if you will.

594
00:25:30.280 --> 00:25:32.920
So John is showing that Jesus is the I am.

595
00:25:32.920 --> 00:25:34.360
He is the Creator.

596
00:25:34.360 --> 00:25:37.480
The book of John begins in the beginning.

597
00:25:37.480 --> 00:25:38.760
Just like Genesis.

598
00:25:38.760 --> 00:25:41.240
You've got these seven statements, these seven signs,

599
00:25:41.240 --> 00:25:42.840
just like the week of creation

600
00:25:42.840 --> 00:25:44.760
pointing to Jesus as the Creator,

601
00:25:44.760 --> 00:25:47.600
the one who's come to bring about a new creation

602
00:25:47.600 --> 00:25:50.200
to give us new life.

603
00:25:51.800 --> 00:25:53.880
When you read and you're thinking about this

604
00:25:53.880 --> 00:25:57.160
in the context of that overarching theme in John,

605
00:25:57.160 --> 00:26:00.400
you think about, well, when God created man,

606
00:26:00.400 --> 00:26:01.580
where did he begin?

607
00:26:03.640 --> 00:26:07.680
He began with the dust of the ground.

608
00:26:08.720 --> 00:26:11.720
This man here is about to be given a new life.

609
00:26:11.720 --> 00:26:13.000
He's been blind from birth.

610
00:26:13.000 --> 00:26:15.440
He's about to see and his life's gonna be completely different

611
00:26:15.440 --> 00:26:17.040
from here on out.

612
00:26:17.040 --> 00:26:20.240
And that begins the Creator reaching down

613
00:26:21.280 --> 00:26:25.000
into the dust of the ground.

614
00:26:25.000 --> 00:26:26.360
And you see that this one who is,

615
00:26:26.360 --> 00:26:28.000
there's another play on words here,

616
00:26:28.000 --> 00:26:30.320
the one who has been sent by God

617
00:26:30.320 --> 00:26:34.040
now sends this man to a pool called sent.

618
00:26:34.040 --> 00:26:35.040
All this is pointing like,

619
00:26:35.040 --> 00:26:40.040
Jesus really is this one who has been sent by God.

620
00:26:40.240 --> 00:26:43.480
And when the blind man passes through the waters,

621
00:26:44.640 --> 00:26:47.000
he goes from blindness to sight,

622
00:26:47.000 --> 00:26:48.320
he goes from darkness to light,

623
00:26:48.320 --> 00:26:52.680
and he steps out with a kind of newness of life.

624
00:26:54.040 --> 00:26:58.160
So this is pointing to what Jesus came to bring about.

625
00:26:58.160 --> 00:27:03.160
He came that we might have new life, eternal life in him,

626
00:27:04.160 --> 00:27:07.360
his healing of this physical blindness,

627
00:27:07.360 --> 00:27:10.960
showing him to be the one who heals spiritual blindness.

628
00:27:10.960 --> 00:27:13.400
Let's think about spiritual blindness a bit more.

629
00:27:14.400 --> 00:27:16.160
It's not just me kind of making the connection here,

630
00:27:16.160 --> 00:27:18.760
by the way, you have chapter nine ending

631
00:27:18.760 --> 00:27:21.000
with Jesus making an explicit statement

632
00:27:21.000 --> 00:27:24.080
that is summarizing the spiritual reality

633
00:27:24.080 --> 00:27:25.840
that's being portrayed by the events

634
00:27:25.840 --> 00:27:27.560
that have just taken place.

635
00:27:27.560 --> 00:27:28.680
So in verse 39, he says,

636
00:27:28.680 --> 00:27:31.640
for judgment I came into this world

637
00:27:31.640 --> 00:27:35.840
that those who do not see may see

638
00:27:35.840 --> 00:27:39.640
and that those who see may become blind.

639
00:27:41.080 --> 00:27:43.880
Then Jesus says at the end,

640
00:27:43.880 --> 00:27:45.880
but now that you say, saying this to the Pharisees,

641
00:27:45.880 --> 00:27:48.320
we see your guilt remains.

642
00:27:48.320 --> 00:27:49.440
So asking, are we blind?

643
00:27:49.440 --> 00:27:51.440
And you say, well, yes,

644
00:27:51.440 --> 00:27:55.000
you're blind in your sinful state.

645
00:27:55.000 --> 00:27:57.520
So what is spiritual blindness then?

646
00:27:57.520 --> 00:27:59.080
Well, spiritual blindness,

647
00:27:59.080 --> 00:28:01.560
but simply as the inability

648
00:28:01.560 --> 00:28:05.340
to truly perceive spiritual reality.

649
00:28:06.840 --> 00:28:11.840
Reminded this week of Plato's allegory of the cave.

650
00:28:11.840 --> 00:28:13.560
I don't know if you've ever come across that.

651
00:28:13.560 --> 00:28:17.560
He talked about life as being like these three men

652
00:28:17.560 --> 00:28:19.720
being chained up in this cave

653
00:28:19.720 --> 00:28:21.320
and they're looking at this wall

654
00:28:21.320 --> 00:28:22.880
and there's a fire behind them

655
00:28:22.880 --> 00:28:26.280
and all they see are these shadows on the wall.

656
00:28:26.280 --> 00:28:28.000
And as far as they know,

657
00:28:28.000 --> 00:28:31.160
these shadows are the only kind of reality that exists.

658
00:28:31.160 --> 00:28:32.720
This is all that they have experienced.

659
00:28:32.720 --> 00:28:36.400
And they're unaware of anything else outside the cave.

660
00:28:36.400 --> 00:28:38.480
One day one of these men are freed.

661
00:28:38.480 --> 00:28:40.880
Their shackles are taken off

662
00:28:40.880 --> 00:28:42.840
and they make their way outside the cave.

663
00:28:42.840 --> 00:28:46.360
And all of a sudden, the world is so expansive.

664
00:28:46.360 --> 00:28:47.600
It's flooded with light.

665
00:28:47.600 --> 00:28:49.200
All these things they had no idea existed.

666
00:28:49.200 --> 00:28:51.680
Now they can see it's been there all along,

667
00:28:51.680 --> 00:28:53.640
but they haven't seen it.

668
00:28:53.640 --> 00:28:54.640
This is real.

669
00:28:54.640 --> 00:28:56.320
This is true.

670
00:28:57.840 --> 00:28:59.360
There was a sense in which like,

671
00:28:59.360 --> 00:29:01.800
yes, those shadows on the wall were true,

672
00:29:01.800 --> 00:29:03.120
but they weren't all that there was.

673
00:29:03.120 --> 00:29:05.720
There was a transcendent reality

674
00:29:05.720 --> 00:29:08.640
beyond what the eyes could see.

675
00:29:08.640 --> 00:29:10.800
And so as the kind of story goes,

676
00:29:10.800 --> 00:29:11.920
he goes back into the cave

677
00:29:11.920 --> 00:29:14.120
and tries to convince these other guys

678
00:29:14.120 --> 00:29:16.400
who are chained up of what they're missing out on.

679
00:29:16.400 --> 00:29:18.960
And they think he's the crazy one.

680
00:29:18.960 --> 00:29:20.160
Because all they've experienced

681
00:29:20.160 --> 00:29:21.360
are these shadows on the wall

682
00:29:21.360 --> 00:29:23.120
and they think he's the one who's lost it

683
00:29:23.120 --> 00:29:24.920
as he describes the light

684
00:29:24.920 --> 00:29:28.680
and beauty that he has seen outside the cave.

685
00:29:29.680 --> 00:29:33.200
And some ways this parable kind of,

686
00:29:33.200 --> 00:29:35.600
this story kind of almost works as a parable

687
00:29:35.600 --> 00:29:39.560
for what we see about spiritual blindness here.

688
00:29:39.560 --> 00:29:42.240
You've got people kind of looking at one layer

689
00:29:42.240 --> 00:29:44.800
of reality in the world.

690
00:29:44.800 --> 00:29:47.520
And it is real, all right?

691
00:29:47.520 --> 00:29:51.120
So this is real, but there is more going on.

692
00:29:51.120 --> 00:29:53.840
There's a spiritual reality that is just as true

693
00:29:53.840 --> 00:29:57.160
as the physical reality that we can see in front of us.

694
00:29:57.640 --> 00:30:00.000
And that spiritual transcendent reality

695
00:30:00.000 --> 00:30:02.520
can be known and experienced.

696
00:30:02.520 --> 00:30:04.120
And how can it be known and experienced

697
00:30:04.120 --> 00:30:07.600
when we are set free by Jesus,

698
00:30:07.600 --> 00:30:10.640
brought into his light?

699
00:30:12.000 --> 00:30:14.080
There's so many people who only see the shadow

700
00:30:14.080 --> 00:30:16.040
and think that's all that there is.

701
00:30:16.040 --> 00:30:17.680
They just don't understand.

702
00:30:18.840 --> 00:30:20.880
They don't perceive.

703
00:30:20.880 --> 00:30:22.240
They're in the dark.

704
00:30:22.240 --> 00:30:23.520
They're spiritually blind.

705
00:30:24.520 --> 00:30:28.280
You see this kind of lack of perception of reality

706
00:30:28.280 --> 00:30:33.280
and how people respond when the blind man is healed here.

707
00:30:33.280 --> 00:30:35.160
We read, first of all, that the neighbors,

708
00:30:35.160 --> 00:30:37.760
they just cannot believe that this has happened.

709
00:30:37.760 --> 00:30:39.120
Like, I know you look like the guy,

710
00:30:39.120 --> 00:30:40.760
but you can't be the guy.

711
00:30:40.760 --> 00:30:41.960
And why can't he be the guy?

712
00:30:41.960 --> 00:30:43.960
Because, well, blind people don't see.

713
00:30:43.960 --> 00:30:45.920
Like, it just doesn't work.

714
00:30:45.920 --> 00:30:47.640
So they don't believe it.

715
00:30:47.640 --> 00:30:48.680
And you've got the Pharisees,

716
00:30:48.680 --> 00:30:50.480
like it's not just that they don't believe it.

717
00:30:50.480 --> 00:30:51.400
They can't believe it.

718
00:30:51.400 --> 00:30:52.480
This cannot be true.

719
00:30:52.640 --> 00:30:54.720
And Jesus definitely can't be sent by God.

720
00:30:54.720 --> 00:30:56.680
No matter how much the evidence points in that direction,

721
00:30:56.680 --> 00:30:58.440
they cannot believe it.

722
00:30:58.440 --> 00:31:01.920
So their lack of perception or understanding shows

723
00:31:01.920 --> 00:31:04.800
that they are blind spiritually.

724
00:31:06.040 --> 00:31:08.760
You've got this conversation with them

725
00:31:08.760 --> 00:31:10.680
and the blind man where he's saying like,

726
00:31:10.680 --> 00:31:11.920
why are you asking me again?

727
00:31:11.920 --> 00:31:14.160
Like, are you wanting to become one of his disciples?

728
00:31:14.160 --> 00:31:17.840
I mean, it's almost comical the way this plays out here.

729
00:31:17.840 --> 00:31:21.120
And their response just shows their blindness,

730
00:31:21.480 --> 00:31:22.920
their pride.

731
00:31:24.680 --> 00:31:25.520
It's obvious.

732
00:31:25.520 --> 00:31:27.120
They're so offended.

733
00:31:27.120 --> 00:31:28.720
They say you were born in utter sin

734
00:31:28.720 --> 00:31:30.840
and you would teach us.

735
00:31:30.840 --> 00:31:32.640
What do you have to teach us?

736
00:31:32.640 --> 00:31:35.000
Kick him out of the synagogue.

737
00:31:35.840 --> 00:31:37.440
So their reaction shows,

738
00:31:37.440 --> 00:31:42.440
not only their inability to perceive spiritual reality,

739
00:31:42.560 --> 00:31:44.760
but their unwillingness too.

740
00:31:44.760 --> 00:31:45.840
Not just that they're not able,

741
00:31:45.840 --> 00:31:46.680
they're not willing.

742
00:31:46.680 --> 00:31:48.440
They don't want it.

743
00:31:48.440 --> 00:31:49.760
They don't want to acknowledge

744
00:31:49.760 --> 00:31:50.720
who Jesus truly is.

745
00:31:50.720 --> 00:31:53.160
Because if they acknowledge

746
00:31:53.160 --> 00:31:55.240
that this is who Jesus truly is,

747
00:31:55.240 --> 00:31:58.080
then they would have to humble themselves.

748
00:31:58.080 --> 00:31:59.840
They'd have to say that they got it wrong.

749
00:31:59.840 --> 00:32:02.960
They would have to be honest about their sin.

750
00:32:04.880 --> 00:32:07.960
Here these guys are with all their titles,

751
00:32:07.960 --> 00:32:10.760
their degrees or all the respect

752
00:32:10.760 --> 00:32:12.520
that they have in the community.

753
00:32:12.520 --> 00:32:14.680
They would have to admit that this guy,

754
00:32:15.640 --> 00:32:16.720
who was blind,

755
00:32:17.480 --> 00:32:19.360
who was beneath them, so to speak,

756
00:32:19.360 --> 00:32:20.920
from their perspective,

757
00:32:20.920 --> 00:32:23.120
they'd have to admit that he was right

758
00:32:23.120 --> 00:32:23.960
and they were wrong.

759
00:32:23.960 --> 00:32:25.680
They don't want that at all.

760
00:32:27.800 --> 00:32:30.280
This is what Jesus said about light

761
00:32:30.280 --> 00:32:32.840
in John chapter three, verses 19 and 20.

762
00:32:33.880 --> 00:32:35.920
He said, this is the judgment

763
00:32:35.920 --> 00:32:37.480
that light has come into the world

764
00:32:37.480 --> 00:32:40.800
and the people loved darkness

765
00:32:40.800 --> 00:32:42.240
rather than the lights,

766
00:32:42.240 --> 00:32:44.280
because their works for evil.

767
00:32:44.280 --> 00:32:46.280
For everyone who does wicked things

768
00:32:46.320 --> 00:32:48.640
hates the light and does not come to the light

769
00:32:48.640 --> 00:32:52.880
lest his works should be exposed.

770
00:32:52.880 --> 00:32:54.880
That's the thing about the light of God.

771
00:32:55.960 --> 00:32:57.920
It exposes.

772
00:32:57.920 --> 00:33:01.240
It shows us for who we truly are.

773
00:33:01.240 --> 00:33:04.280
It reveals what is hidden in the darkness.

774
00:33:04.280 --> 00:33:08.400
We all do prefer to keep our sin hidden away.

775
00:33:08.400 --> 00:33:10.320
Like we love the darkness rather than light

776
00:33:10.320 --> 00:33:13.280
because we want to keep those things hidden.

777
00:33:13.280 --> 00:33:16.760
God's light reveals our ignorance,

778
00:33:16.760 --> 00:33:19.120
sinfulness, or pride.

779
00:33:20.920 --> 00:33:21.880
That light shines.

780
00:33:21.880 --> 00:33:22.720
We've got an option.

781
00:33:22.720 --> 00:33:25.400
Are we gonna run to the shadows?

782
00:33:25.400 --> 00:33:27.280
Are we gonna run to Jesus?

783
00:33:28.200 --> 00:33:31.240
Good news is then the light of Christ

784
00:33:31.240 --> 00:33:33.760
shows us who he is

785
00:33:33.760 --> 00:33:34.960
and what he has done for us

786
00:33:34.960 --> 00:33:37.440
that we might be forgiven and reconciled to God.

787
00:33:39.080 --> 00:33:40.520
Even today, like as we're thinking about

788
00:33:40.520 --> 00:33:42.680
the light of God shining us

789
00:33:42.680 --> 00:33:44.560
as we're seeing this in his word,

790
00:33:45.680 --> 00:33:49.080
are we willing to be honest about our sinfulness

791
00:33:49.080 --> 00:33:50.840
to confess that before God?

792
00:33:53.080 --> 00:33:54.720
Are we gonna hide in the shadows?

793
00:33:56.080 --> 00:33:57.640
Are we gonna stay in the dark?

794
00:33:57.640 --> 00:33:59.280
Are we gonna run to the light of Christ

795
00:33:59.280 --> 00:34:01.520
to know the forgiveness and cleansing

796
